the world wide web wanderer also referred to as just the wanderer was a perl based web crawler that was first deployed in june 1993 to measure the size of the world wide web it was used to generate an index called the wandex later in 1993 while the wanderer was probably the first web robot and with its index clearly had the potential to become a general purpose www search engine the author does not make this claim 1 and elsewhere 2 it is stated that this was not its purpose the wanderer charted the growth of the web until late 1995 edit references matt gray s home page pertinent page on matt gray s section on mit site brian lamacchia s phd thesis section 1 2 3 edit external links growth of the web report early mention of the world wide web wanderer 